THIRD-PARTY COBOL SOURCE ATTRIBUTION
================================================================================

The generated Java programs in src/main/java/com/lazarus/cobol/generated/ were
transpiled from the following COBOL sources. The COBOL source code is NOT
included in this repository — only the transpiled Java output is present.

1. GnuCOBOL Test Suite (1,224 programs)
   Source: https://gnucobol.sourceforge.io/
   License: GNU General Public License (GPL) v3 / Lesser GPL v3
   Note: The generated Java is an independent transformation, not a
   modification of GnuCOBOL itself. GnuCOBOL is a compiler, and the test
   programs are inputs to validate compiler behavior.

2. AWS CardDemo (44 programs)
   Source: https://github.com/aws-samples/aws-mainframe-modernization-carddemo
   Copyright: Amazon.com, Inc. or its affiliates
   License: Apache License, Version 2.0
   Note: CardDemo is Amazon's reference enterprise CICS/VSAM application.
   The original COBOL is Apache 2.0 licensed. The transpiled Java output
   is a derivative work.

3. CMS Medicare Pricers (55 programs)
   Source: https://www.cms.gov/medicare/payment
   Copyright: U.S. Government (Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services)
   License: Public domain (U.S. Government work, 17 U.S.C. Section 105)
   Note: Federal government COBOL programs are not subject to copyright.
